{
  "id": "phekb-diabetic-retinopathy-comprehensive",
  "source": "phekb",
  "source_id": "diabetic-retinopathy",
  "name": "Diabetic Retinopathy - Comprehensive Provider Query (DX + Meds + Procedures)",
  "description": "Simulates an ophthalmologist identifying their complete diabetic retinopathy patient population. Combines: DR diagnosis codes, anti-VEGF injections, and fundoscopic procedures. Tests Condition + MedicationRequest + Procedure union for diabetes complication.",
  "prompt": "I need to identify my complete diabetic retinopathy patient population for a quality improvement initiative on screening adherence and anti-VEGF treatment monitoring. From clinical experience, DR patients are documented in different ways: most have a formal DR diagnosis (proliferative, nonproliferative, or with macular edema), some are on anti-VEGF intravitreal injections (ranibizumab, aflibercept, bevacizumab), and most have undergone fundoscopic eye examination.\n\nPlease run multiple FHIR queries to capture the full population:\n1. Patients with any diabetic retinopathy diagnosis\n2. Patients prescribed anti-VEGF injections\n3. Patients who have undergone camera fundoscopy\n\nFor each query, return the matching resources. I want the union of all patients found. Note: DR is a complication of diabetes, so all DR patients should also have a diabetes diagnosis on their problem list.",
  "metadata": {
    "implementation_guide": "US Core 5.0.0",
    "multi_query": true,
    "algorithm_path": "comprehensive",
    "algorithm_path_description": "Union of DR dx + anti-VEGF Rx + fundoscopy Procedure. Tests Condition + MedicationRequest + Procedure cross-resource union for diabetes complication.",
    "expected_queries": [
      "Condition?code=http://snomed.info/sct|4855003,http://snomed.info/sct|59276001,http://snomed.info/sct|390834004,http://snomed.info/sct|1551000119108,http://snomed.info/sct|312912001",
      "MedicationRequest?code=http://www.nlm.nih.gov/research/umls/rxnorm|595060,http://www.nlm.nih.gov/research/umls/rxnorm|1232150,http://www.nlm.nih.gov/research/umls/rxnorm|253337",
      "Procedure?code=http://snomed.info/sct|314971001"
    ],
    "code_systems": [
